			<h2>Neighborhood</h2>
			<p>Welcome to our neighborhood! We picked out some things that you might like.</p>
			<h3>See</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong><a href="http://bpca.ny.gov/places/parks/">Battery Park City Esplanade</a></strong>: Walk up and down the Hudson; nice any time of day.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.seaglasscarousel.nyc/">Sea Glass Carousel</a></strong>: Most beautiful in the evening, but it's open all day.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="https://oneworldobservatory.com/">One World Trade</a></strong>: Tickets to the observatory are spendy, so skip that and just walk around the grounds of the tallest building in the western hemisphere.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liberty_Park_(Manhattan)">Liberty Park</a></strong>: New park overlooking WTC has a touch of High Line.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://ny.curbed.com/wtc-transportation-hub">The Oculus</a></strong>: The crazy transportation center designed like a bird taking flight.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.siferry.com/">Staten Island Ferry</a></strong>: Free ferry ride leaves every half-hour. Beautiful views, goes by Statue of Liberty.</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Shop</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong><a href="https://brookfieldplaceny.com/">Brookfield Place</a></strong>: Don't call it a mall. (It's a mall.)</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.ledistrict.com/">Le District</a></strong>: Don't call it a "French Eataly." (Yeah.)</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.southstreetseaport.com/">South Street Seaport</a></strong>: Directly on the other side of Manhattan from us, a 15-minute walk.</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>EaT & DrinK</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong><a href="https://www.shakeshack.com/location/battery-park-city/">Shake Shack</a></strong>: Michelle has been known to enjoy their cheese fries occasionally.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.ledistrict.com/le-bar.cfm">Le Bar</a></strong>: Sunset + waterfront + drinks + oysters + fries. We're there every Friday in the summer: <a href="https://www.instagram.com/explore/tags/batteryparkfridays/" target="_blank">#BatteryParkFridays</a>.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://newyork.amadarestaurant.com/">Amada</a></strong>: Our new favorite place â€” fantastic tapas with outdoor seating, like you were on the shores of Andalusia.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.locandaverdenyc.com/">Locanda Verde</a></strong>: Don't miss the sheep's milk ricotta (Rex's favorite). You'll want a reservation for this one.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="https://brookfieldplaceny.com/directory/food">Hudson Eats</a></strong>: Good for something quick. Food court includes <b>Black Seed Bagels</b>, <b>Umami Burger</b>, <b>Little Muenster</b>, <b>Blue Ribbon Sushi</b> &mdash; can't go wrong.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.parmnyc.com/location/battery-park-city/">Parm</a></strong>: Hopefully the mozz sticks will be back on the menu by then.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.piera.com/">Pier A</a></strong>: Gaze out on the Statue of Liberty and have a drink. Close to the Sea Glass Carousel.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.inattesopizzabar.com/">Inatteso Pizzabar Casano</a></strong>: Our favorite pizza in the 'hood.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.elveznyc.com/">El Vez</a></strong>: Kitchy Mexican with lots of cheese.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.eveningbar.com/">Evening Bar</a></strong>: Chill spot in Tribeca. Next to <a href="http://www.littlepark.com/" target="_blank">Little Park</a>.</li>
				<li><strong><a href="http://www.conradnewyork.com/dine/loopy-doopy-rooftop-bar/">Loopy Doopy</a></strong>: Rooftop bar atop the <a href="http://www.conradnewyork.com/" target="_blank">Conrad</a>.</li>
			</ul>
